==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thymol
<hw>Thym"ol</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Thym</ets>e +
<ets>-ol</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A phenol derivative of
cymene, <chform>C10H13.OH</chform>, isomeric with carvacrol, found in
oil of thyme, and extracted as a white crystalline substance of a
pleasant aromatic odor and strong antiseptic properties; -- called also
<altname>hydroxy cymene</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>thymus</ent>⟦br⟧
